#: ../../src/whatsnew/1.2.rst:42
msgid "Security changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/whatsnew/1.2.rst:44
msgid ""
"The interface to the ``_users`` and ``_replicator`` databases have been "
"changed so that non-administrator users can see less information:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/whatsnew/1.2.rst:47
msgid "In the ``_users`` database:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/whatsnew/1.2.rst:49
msgid ""
"User documents can now only be read by the respective users, as well as "
"administrators. Other users cannot read these documents."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/whatsnew/1.2.rst:51
msgid "Views can only be defined and queried by administrator users."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/whatsnew/1.2.rst:52
msgid "The ``_changes`` feed can only be queried by administrator users."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/whatsnew/1.2.rst:54
msgid "In the ``_replicator`` database:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/whatsnew/1.2.rst:56
msgid ""
"Documents now have a forced ``owner`` field that corresponds to the "
"authenticated user that created them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/whatsnew/1.2.rst:58
msgid ""
"Non-owner users will not see confidential information like passwords or "
"OAuth tokens in replication documents; they can still see the other contents"
" of those documents. Administrators can see everything."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/whatsnew/1.2.rst:61
msgid "Views can only be defined and queried by administrators."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/whatsnew/1.2.rst:64
msgid "Database Compression"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/whatsnew/1.2.rst:66
msgid ""
"The new optional (but enabled by default) compression of disk files requires"
" an upgrade of the on-disk format (5 -> 6) which occurs on creation for new "
"databases and views, and on compaction for existing files. This format is "
"not supported in previous releases, so rollback would require replication to"
" the previous CouchDB release or restoring from backup."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/whatsnew/1.2.rst:72
msgid ""
"Compression can be disabled by setting ``compression = none`` in your "
"``local.ini`` ``[couchdb]`` section, but the on-disk format will still be "
"upgraded."
msgstr ""

